    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rt7",
      "x": 90,
      "y": 725,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 120,
      "text": "TRANSPIRATION\n• Evaporation from aerial parts\n  (mainly stomata in leaves)\n• Stomata: OPEN (day) / CLOSED (night)\n• Guard cells turgid → stoma opens\n• Guard cells flaccid → stoma closes\n• Creates transpiration pull",
      "originalText": "TRANSPIRATION\n• Evaporation from aerial parts\n  (mainly stomata in leaves)\n• Stomata: OPEN (day) / CLOSED (night)\n• Guard cells turgid → stoma opens\n• Guard cells flaccid → stoma closes\n• Creates transpiration pull",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
